A friend sent me this video tonight so I had to reshare it. She didn’t know that I wasn’t feeling my best on today, but when I tell you this lifted my spirit OMG. It took me back to the day when I was in the abortion clinic getting ready to terminate the pregnancy of my son. I will never forget the nurse that came in the room and told me, I can get fired for telling you this but, “ God anointed you and you have a major purpose on your life, and your son inside of you will be a prophet to the nations”. When the doctors come back in the room and asked me was I ready, I told him to give me a minute and I went to the bathroom and I looked in the mirror and cried. I had a conversation with God in the abortion clinic; he told me don’t worry about that other may think, I AM with you. I went back to the room and told the doctor I can’t do this. I thank God for using that nurse to speak to me. Believe it or not my son who will be 14, has gotten me through some of the toughest times in my life. I just thank God for the anointing and the purpose of both of our lives. I hope this message encourages someone. No matter what your situation looks like God still have a purpose on your life…….. CeCe Ivory

Entering a relationship, marriage or partnership solely based on you thinking a person is a good person, is not always the best thing to do. Take this next chapter of your life and really analyze the person that you’re interested in, and see if they match up with the life that you’ve already worked hard for. Some people will enter a relationship with you just to gain what you have, without going after it for themselves. Some people will even date and marry you to increase their level of success, while drain and take everything from you. What is their motive for dating you, if they have nothing? These are questions that you need to ask yourself, and them. Yes, relationships and marriage is about teamwork and partnership. But what happens when you’re the force all by itself, and they have nothing to bring to the table. They may not have everything that you have, but they have to come with something. Stop settling for mediocre relationships, when you can have what it is that you truly deserve. 
-CeCe Ivory
